cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video analysis and dynamic texture recognition. The use of spatio-temporal receptive fields also suggests a focus on image and video processing. The paper also mentions the use of handcrafted and learned primitives, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The evaluation of the proposed approach using regional statistics and joint histograms suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of time-causal recognition and time-recursive formulation suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
